<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf182f8a6-d790-11f0-bdae-a8987afac842" identifier="/us/usc/t27/s218"><num value="218">§ 218.</num><heading> Civil penalties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person who violates the provisions of this subchapter shall be subject to a civil penalty of not more than $10,000, and each day shall constitute a separate offense.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf182f8a7-d790-11f0-bdae-a8987afac842">(<ref href="/us/act/1935-08-29/ch814">Aug. 29, 1935, ch. 814</ref>, title II, § 207, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/690/tVIII/s8001/a/3">Pub. L. 100–690, title VIII, § 8001(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1988-11-18">Nov. 18, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4520">102 Stat. 4520</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
